sec.p:
Each mode input pattern for each station contained a set of daily values for prediction of
\documentclass{aastex}\usepackage{amsbsy}\usepackage{amsfonts}\usepackage{amssymb}\usepackage{bm}\usepackage{mathrsfs}\usepackage{pifont}\usepackage{stmaryrd}\usepackage{textcomp}\usepackage{portland, xspace}\usepackage{amsmath, amsxtra}\pagestyle{empty}\DeclareMathSizes {10} {9} {7} {6} \begin{document} $$Di \ ( i = 1 , 2 , \ldots 5 )$$ \end{document}
or A5 from a specific station. One value was applied to both the current and subsequent day and where the final value was the specific PM 10 IAQI monitoring station under consideration. Therefore, each neural mode input pattern had a total of 15 values: average temperature ( T), relative humidity ( RH), wind speed ( WS), barometric pressure ( P), rainfall amount ( RF), sunshine duration ( SD) from St-M, the Construction Influence Index of n construction sites ( Ci), and the PM 10 IAQI
